    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "This hadith, transmitted through Imam al-Sadiq (AS) from the Prophet Muhammad (SAWW), contrasts two types of people: those blessed with long life who fill it with good deeds, whose ending is joyful because their Lord is pleased with them; and those with long life who fill it with evil deeds, whose ending is grievous because their Lord is angry with them. The teaching emphasizes that longevity alone is not a blessing - it is how one uses their time that determines their fate.",
        "key_terms": {
          "طُوبَى": "Tuba: blessed, fortunate; also the name of a tree in Paradise",
          "مُنْقَلَب": "Munqalab: ending, final destination, outcome"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did the Prophet say about those who live long lives with good deeds vs evil deeds?"
